This paper deals with the problem of approximating the size of set union, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of biased random generators and the analysis of approximation ratios suggest that this paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithmic techniques used in this paper, such as randomized approximation and adaptive access to input sets, are common in the field of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
